EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to transportation; designating State Route 163 as
the Colorado River Highway; designating the bridge
connecting State Route 163 with Bullhead City, Arizona,
as the Donald J. Laughlin Memorial Bridge; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law provides designations for certain highways in this State. (NRS
2 408.303, 408.307; Chapter 71, Statutes of Nevada 1987, at page 136) This bill
3 designates: (1) State Route 163 as the Colorado River Highway; and (2) the bridge
4 connecting State Route 163 with Bullhead City, Arizona, as the Donald J. Laughlin
5 Memorial Bridge. This bill also requires the Director of the Department of
6 Transportation to place suitable markers along the highway and bridge in locations
7 where the Director deems appropriate.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 408 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto the provisions set forth as sections 2 and 3 of this act.
3 Sec. 2. 1. State Route 163, as now or hereafter located in
4 this State, is designated as the Colorado River Highway.
5 2. The Director shall place suitable markers along State
6 Route 163 and may locate them at such points as the Director
7 deems appropriate.
